metadata.name: Tomoe Gozen
metadata.description:
Tomoe Gozen was one of the most feared female samurai warriors in Japanese history. She was a female martial artist with the title "Onna-bugeisha".

Tomoe Gozen was extremely frightening on the battlefield. She fought to the death and bravely, she. The troops under her command trusted their instincts and followed her orders. Her reputation for her competence quickly spread throughout Japan. Tomoe Gozen, an outstanding female warrior, was honored as Japan's first female general.

Tomoe Gozen has never let those who trust her down. In 1184, she led her army into battle and led 300 samurai warriors against 2,000 warriors of the Taira clan. Tomoe Gozen was one of the five survivors at the end of this war.
